{{Infobox video game | title = Entrepreneur | developer = [[Stardock Systems]] | publisher = Stardock Systems | platforms = [[OS/2]], [[Windows]] | released = October 10, 1997 | genre = Strategy }}
'''''Entrepreneur''''' is a 1997 [[Business simulation game|business simulation]] [[video game]].
== Gameplay == The game sees the player build a successful company and [[Monopoly|dominate the market]] through [[corporate warfare]]. Players need to research, manufacture, and market their products better than their [[Business competition|competitors]], and when in financial trouble they can seek help from criminal figures.
== Critical reception == Jacob Proffitt of ''[[Gamezilla]]'' praised the core idea behind the game, but said that it failed in its execution.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gamezilla.com/reviews/e/entrepreneur.asp|title=Entrepreneur by Stardock. Reviewed by Jacob Proffitt|date=2000-12-07|access-date=2017-02-04|deadurl=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20001207102700/http://www.gamezilla.com/reviews/e/entrepreneur.asp|archivedate=2000-12-07|df=}}</ref> ''[[GameSpot|GameSpo]]''t's Tim McDonald too appreciated the novel idea of having a strategy game where the weapon is [[Business deal|business deal<nowiki/>s]] not tanks, but criticised the "fussy interface and nebulous economics".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/entrepreneur-review/1900-2535830/|title=Entrepreneur Review|newspaper=GameSpot|language=en|access-date=2017-02-04}}</ref>
