{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
[[File:Jacob Letterstedt.jpg|thumb|Jacob Letterstedt]]
'''Jacob Letterstedt''' (1796 – 1862), born '''Lallerstedt''' in [[Östergötland]], was a [[Sweden|Swedish]] businessman who settled in the [[Cape Colony]] (part of present-day [[South Africa]]). He arrived at [[Cape Town]] in 1820, where he made his fortune in the grain trade. Later he founded the company that became [[South African Breweries]]. In 1841 he was appointed Consul of [[Sweden-Norway]].

Letterstedt donated money to several prizes and to the [[Letterstedt Association]], which promotes Nordic cooperation. In 1860, he was elected a member of the [[Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences]].

